The paper presents a novel approach for visual-inertial SLAM, which is a topic related to robotics and computer vision. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses filtering and optimization methods, which are common in machine learning and computer vision, suggesting cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with sensor fusion and estimation, which are relevant to control systems, indicating cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible sub-category.
